title: Los Angeles goes car free for a day for CicLAvia
text: Angel Cruz from San Franando Valley rides his bike named Timmy along the streets of downtown Los Angeles on Sunday. It’s a car free day in parts of LA and some six miles of streets in and around downtown Los Angeles are closed to motor vehicles as the city’s fifth anniversary celebration of the CicLAvia festival opens the lanes to cyclists. Richard Vogel — The Associated Press
